Recently, Saint Andrew Charity Foundation realized «Children's Dreams» Project.

Forty children of socially unprotected categories of families, kids from children's homes of the family type enjoyed the fascinating world of entertainment, visited various attractions of the park «Happylon». Children received a lot of positive emotions, an unlimited number of unforgettable impressions and incredible moments. Saturday, 13th May 2017 Ms Tshering Yangzom the Principal of Tiny Toes Daycare has been a ardent supporter of Badum, this will be her third distribution of the clay piggy banks (Badum) to the children of her school Tiny Toes Daycare 🐷
.

Our Badum distribution on Saturday coincided with their pre 'Mother's Day' celebration in the daycare, a potluck gathering of the parents and children who sang for their mothers and each gave an individual footprint card to their mothers, with a poem on it. A fruitful morning spent with the children of Tiny Toes Daycare who painted their Badums 🐷
.
Ms Tshering believes, it is never too early to instill the values of sharing among children and today's activity will make the entire process more personal. These are values that can be taught and hopefully one day passed down to a younger generation, in the near future 🐷
.

Tiny Toes daycare also has close 14 scholarship children, an effort that is very dear to the Principal's heart and is always looking for funds to help support children from the nearby slum areas 🐷
.
A brief about Aum Badum, Badum is a little clay pig that encourages young Bhutanese children to save money, and when she is full to return her to the YDF (The Youth Development Fund) so that the money may be used for YDF’s many programmes, among which include scholarships for needy students as well as drug rehabilitation programmes. SAVE TO SHARE 🐷
.
To HELP the the under privilege youth of Bhutan and to know more about The Bhutan Youth Development Fund visit www.bhutanyouth.org 🐷
.

#China–#UnitedStates #relations, more often known as U.S.–Chinese relations, #Chinese–U.S. relations, or #Sino-#American relations, refer to #international relations between the United States of #America and the #People's #Republic of #China (#PRC). The partnership between China and the #UnitedStates, in which each nation regards the other as a potential #adversary as well as a #strategic #partner, has been described by #world #leaders and #academics as the world's most important #bilateral relationship of the century. As of 2017, the United States has the world's #largest #economy and China the second largest.
